  It was a cold winter’s day that Sunday. The parking lot to the (1)_____ was filling up quickly. I noticed, as I got out of my car, fellow church members were (2)_____ among themselves as they walked in the church.\n  As I got (3)_____ I saw a man leaning up against the wall outside the church. He was almost lying down (4)_____ he was asleep. His hat was (5)_____ down so you could not see his face. He wore shoes that looked ten years old, too （6） for his feet, with holes all over them, his toes （7）_____ out.\n  I guessed this man was （8）_____ , and asleep, so I walked on （9）_____ through the doors of the church.\n  We all talked for a few minutes, and someone （10）_____ the man lying outside.  People whispered but no one took the （11）_____ to ask him to come in, （12）_____ me.\n  A few moments later church began. We all waited for the Preacher （牧师） to take his （13）_____ and to give us the Word, （14）_____ the doors to the church opened.\n  In （15)_____ the homeless man walking down the church with his head down.\n\n  1. A. school B. lecture C. park D. church\n  2. A. arguing B. whispering C. staring D. speaking\n  3. A. closer B. clearer C. lower D. farther\n  4. A. even though B. so that C. as if D. even if\n  5. A. dragged B. pulled C. dropped D. pushed\n  6. A. big B. bad C. ugly D. small\n  7. A. reached B. went C. stuck D. run\n  8. A. homeless B. helpless C. hopeless D. careless\n  9. A. out B. by C. off D. from\n  10. A. invited B. mentioned C. took D. called\n  11. A. pleasure B. measure C. courage D. trouble\n  12. A. except B. besides C. without D. including\n  13. A. turn B. place C. time D. seat\n  14. A. when B. before C. as D. after\n  15. A. rushed B. ran C. came D. went\n解析：\n1. D. church。句意：那个星期日的教堂停车场很快就被填满了。fill up quickly“很快被填满”是可以推想出这里指的是一个聚集人们的地方。\n2. B. whispering。句意：当我下车时，教堂的其他教友正在低声交谈着走进教堂。whispering是低声交谈，不打扰别人的一种方式。\n3. A. closer。句意：当我走近时，我看到一个人靠在教堂外的墙上。get close意思是“接近”。\n4. C. as if。句意：他几乎躺下了好像正在睡觉。as if意思是“好像”。\n5. B. pulled。句意：他的帽子压得很低，所以你看不到他的脸。pull down是“压低”的意思。\n6. A. big。句意：他穿的鞋看起来十年旧了，太大了，形成所有穿的地方，脚趾露了出来。此处 big指鞋子很大，不合脚。\n7. C. stuck。句意：他穿的鞋看起来十年旧了，太大了，形成所有穿的地方，脚趾露了出来。toe stuck out指脚趾露出来。\n8. A. homeless。句意：我猜测那个人是无家可归的，并且正在睡觉，所以我穿过教堂的大门。整体句意为推测那个人睡在教堂外的时候应该是无家可归的人。\n9. D. from。句意：所以我穿过教堂的大门。从原地到教堂是from，不是其他选项。\n10. D. called。句意：我们都聊了几分钟，有人叫了一声在外面躺着的那个人。此处是someone called the man lying外面的人。\n11. C. courage。句意：人们窃窃私语但没有人有勇气去叫他进来，包括我在内。Courage “勇气”。\n12. A. except。句意：包括我在内，没有人有勇气去叫他进来。except me是“除我之外”。\n13. D. seat。句意：几分钟后，礼拜开始了，我们都等待牧师坐在他的位子上给我们讲道。take his seat指坐到牧的席位上。\n14. B. before。句意：我们都等待牧师坐在他的席位上给我们讲道，这时教堂的大门打开了。before“在……之前”\n15. C. came。句意：当教堂的大门打开时，一个无家可归的人走进了教堂，低着头。come 指“走进来”。